Use only MCP tools. No Python code.

Objective: Generate Test cases for User Story

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

STEP 1 — READ USER STORY FILE

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Use the filesystem MCP tool to read the user story file:

user-story-compliance.md

from the current project folder (Testable_PoC).

Understand every validation, acceptance criteria, positive,

negative, boundary, UI/UX, and accessibility section.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

STEP 2 — GENERATE TEST CASES

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Generate test cases covering ALL sections of the user story:

1. Acceptance Criteria tests

2. Positive Validation tests

3. Negative Validation tests

4. Boundary Value Analysis tests

5. UI/UX Validation tests

6. Accessibility Validation tests

For each test case produce:

  TITLE       : TC-<number> — <short, clear test case name>

  DESCRIPTION : <what this test case verifies, one sentence>

  TEST STEPS  : Each step has three parts:

                  Action        — what the tester does

                  Test Data     — exact input, URL, or value used

                  Expected Result — what the system should do

                                   after this specific action

RULES:

- Expected Result must NOT appear in the Description field

- Expected Result belongs ONLY in the Test Steps CSV column

- Every step must have its own Expected Result

- Minimum 3 steps per test case, maximum 20 steps

- Test Data column can be empty if no specific data is needed

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

STEP 3 — SAVE AS CSV (XRAY IMPORT FORMAT)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Use the filesystem MCP tool to save two files:

FILE 1 — JIRA ISSUE CREATION CSV

Filename: test-cases-<story-name>.csv

This creates the Test issues in JIRA.

Columns (exact header row):

Summary,Issue Type,Priority,Description,Labels

Example rows:

"TC-001 — Valid Login with Email","Test","Medium","Verifies that a registered user can log in using a valid email and password combination","regression"

"TC-002 — Invalid Password Error","Test","Medium","Verifies that an incorrect password displays an appropriate error message","regression"

FILE 2 — XRAY STEPS CSV (Add Steps import)

Filename: test-steps-<story-name>.csv

This imports the test steps into each Test issue via Xray.

Columns (exact header row):

TC ID,Summary,Step,Action,Data,Expected Result

Example rows (one row per step):

"TC-001","Valid Login with Email","1","Navigate to /signin page","https://app.testable.io/signin","Sign-in page loads with email field, password field and Authenticate button visible"

"TC-001","Valid Login with Email","2","Enter valid email in the email field","test@testable.cloud","Email is accepted with no validation error shown"

"TC-001","Valid Login with Email","3","Enter valid password in the password field","Test@1234!","Password is masked and field shows no error"

"TC-001","Valid Login with Email","4","Click the Authenticate button","—","Loading spinner appears on button and button is disabled"

"TC-001","Valid Login with Email","5","Wait for API response","—","User is redirected to /dashboard with welcome toast message"

FILE 3 — REVIEW MARKDOWN

Filename: test-cases-review-<story-name>.md

A human-readable version for review before JIRA push.

Format:

## TC-001 — Valid Login with Email

**Description:** Verifies that a registered user can successfully sign in.

**Priority:** Medium

**Labels:** regression

| Step | Action | Test Data | Expected Result |

|------|--------|-----------|-----------------|

| 1 | Navigate to /signin | https://app.testable.io/signin | Page loads correctly |

| 2 | Enter valid email | test@testable.cloud | Accepted, no error |

| 3 | ... | ... | ... |

